132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST SPECIAL SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 1668
S.P. 663 In Senate, April 17, 2025
An Act Regarding the Voting Requirement to Extend the Date for
Adjournment of the Legislature
Reference to the Committee on State and Local Government suggested and ordered printed.
DAREK M. GRANT
Secretary of the Senate
Presented by Senator DUSON of Cumberland.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 3 MRSA §2, 2nd ¶, as amended by PL 2019, c. 475, §11, is further amended
3 to read:
4 The first regular session of the Legislature, after its convening, shall may not adjourn
5 no later than the 3rd Wednesday in June and the 2nd regular session of the Legislature shall
6 may not adjourn no later than the 3rd Wednesday in April. The Legislature, in case of
7 emergency, may by a the affirmative vote of 2/3 a majority of the members of each House
8 present and voting, extend the date for adjournment for the first or 2nd regular session by
9 no more than 5 legislative days, and in case of further emergency, may by a the affirmative
10 vote of 2/3 a majority of the members of each House present and voting, further extend the
11 date for adjournment by 5 additional legislative days. The times for adjournment for the
12 first and 2nd regular sessions may also be extended for one additional legislative day for
13 the purpose of considering possible objections of the Governor to any bill or resolution
14 presented to the Governor by the Legislature under the Constitution of Maine, Article IV,
15 Part Third, Section 2.
16 SUMMARY
1177 This bill removes the requirement that a vote to extend the length of a regular session
1188 of the Legislature beyond the statutory adjournment date be done by 2/3 of the members of
1199 the Senate and House present and voting and instead requires an affirmative vote of a
2200 majority of the members of the Senate and House present and voting.
